org.openhubframework.openhub.api.entity

Class Request

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhubframework.openhub.api.entity.SuperEntity<Long>
      • org.openhubframework.openhub.api.entity.Request
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, HumanReadable, Identifiable<Long>

    @Entity
public class Request
extends SuperEntity<Long>
    Entity for saving request with external system or during internal communication.

    Request is uniquely identified by its URI and response join ID. Both these attributes helps to join right request and response together.

    Since:
    0.4
    Author:
    Petr Juza
    See Also:
    Response, Serialized Form

        public String getResponseJoinId()
        Gets identifier for pairing/joining request and response together. It can be Message or correlation ID or exchange ID or some ID that is unique with getUri() uri. This attribute helps to associate response to the right request.
